JD 1:

Principal Duties & Responsibilities
1. Global Category Management

Champion global commercial category management processes including diversity, sustainability, risk, currency, and continuity aligned with business KPIs.

Provide thought leadership on sourcing strategies in collaboration with business stakeholders and procurement operations.

Manage global supplier relationships and product portfolios, driving cost reductions, leveraging scale, and establishing SOPs for knowledge transfer.

Own supplier qualification, selection, contract development (with Legal), implementation, compliance, and ongoing supplier base management.

Lead RFP/RFQ processes as appropriate using sourcing tools (e.g., Jaggaer).

Develop and drive 3‑ to 5‑year global sourcing strategies that meet both category and business partner goals.

Assess market intelligence and leverage predictive analytics to inform strategic decisions.

Participate in supplier business reviews and key pharmaceutical industry events.

Remove organizational silos and support the global sharing of category insights.

2. Procurement Partnering

Proactively engage with Global Business Partners and functional stakeholders to define category strategy requirements.

Create communication mechanisms to coordinate internal stakeholders and report on sourcing impact.

Drive adoption of global sourcing strategies across the enterprise and ensure collaboration across teams.

Work closely with the internal Global Pharma Category team and Procurement Value Enablement to share expertise across category areas (APIs, Biologics, Injectables, OTC/Other).

Mentor and develop junior talent through coaching and inclusion in strategy activities.

3. Scale of Responsibilities / Strategic Impact

Achieve measurable reductions in total cost of ownership without compromising quality, service levels, or supply continuity.

Serve as the key category interface with all levels within Fresenius organization to align strategies and financial targets.

Own multi‑year category strategy objectives, timelines, and KPIs.

Analyze cross‑divisional spending and develop global strategic plans to reduce cost of ownership across business units.

Encourage use of eSourcing, Spend Visibility, AI integration, learning platforms, and R2P tools enterprise‑wide.

Partner with Procurement, Supply Chain, and Operations to harness insights from financial planning, forecasting, P&L performance, tariffs, and inflation.

Track and report category performance metrics, including spend under contract and payment terms, and drive continuous improvement.

Own and present at pharma‑related meetings and leadership presentations.

Manage ongoing and new contracts to ensure they are robust and aligned with organizational standards and objectives.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JD 2:

Key Responsibilities

Assist in identifying, qualifying, and onboarding new manufacturers across generics (especially injectables).
Coordinate pricing, supply terms, and rebate agreements under leadership guidance.
Maintain supplier scorecards, track performance, and ensure compliance with quality and continuity requirements.
Partner with sales, customer solutions, and account management teams to identify product opportunities.
Provide data, pricing, and product insights to help structure and close deals.
Track customer uptake and identify opportunities to expand share within key accounts.
Gather and analyze market intelligence (WAC, ASP, competitor pricing) to inform pricing recommendations.
Maintain pricing models and dashboards; assist leadership in dynamic price adjustments.
Monitor industry and competitive developments to provide timely insights that influence sourcing and pricing strategy.
Work closely with supply chain, finance, regulatory, and sales teams to ensure sourcing activities align with customer commitments and internal processes.
Support coordination of product launches, allocations, and customer communications.
Contribute to internal education on product positioning and market conditions.
Support monthly financial tracking, forecasting, and variance analysis for the pharma portfolio.
Assist in annual target setting and business planning processes.
Provide regular updates on key metrics such as gross margin, sales trends, and supplier performance.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JD 3:

Global Category Management & Strategic Sourcing

Own and execute global category strategy for assigned pharma categories (e.g., APIs, CMOs, CRO services, lab consumables), translating global strategy into regional/country-specific implementation plans.

Lead sourcing and supplier selection for clinical, medical, or manufacturing categories, ensuring compliance with regulatory and quality standards.

Continuously monitor supplier markets, pricing trends, and emerging solutions to optimize supplier footprint and cost-effectiveness.

Develop and implement category-specific procurement frameworks, processes, and tools to harmonize sourcing practices globally.

Supplier Management & Performance

Manage relationships with key global and regional suppliers, ensuring contract compliance, timely delivery, and continuous performance improvement.

Lead supplier performance evaluations, track KPIs, and implement corrective actions for quality, delivery, or compliance issues.

Collaborate with suppliers to identify innovation, cost-saving, and process improvement opportunities aligned with pharma regulatory requirements.

Contracting & Compliance

Lead drafting, negotiation, and execution of supplier contracts including master service agreements, licensing agreements, and clinical trial services contracts.

Ensure contracts define scope, pricing, service levels, compliance, and risk management clearly.

Manage the contract lifecycle, including renewals, amendments, and audits for regulatory and corporate compliance.

Procurement Operations & Budget Management

Oversee purchase order creation, verification, and requisition approvals for pharma categories, ensuring accuracy and adherence to budgets.

Track procurement costs, monitor budget alignment, and report on savings, spend, and value delivery.

Ensure all procurement activities comply with global/regional regulatory requirements and internal policies.

Cross-functional Collaboration

Work closely with R&D, Clinical Operations, Manufacturing, and Medical Affairs teams to align sourcing strategies with business needs.

Engage stakeholders early to ensure transparency, buy-in, and consistent implementation of global category strategies.

Support knowledge-sharing by updating SOPs, guidelines, and knowledge base articles specific to pharma procurement categories.

Tools & Analytics

Utilize procurement systems and tools (e.g., SAP Ariba, Coupa, VMS) to track supplier performance, manage contracts, and identify savings opportunities.

Provide market intelligence, trend analysis, and reporting to drive data-backed category decisions.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
JD 4:

Key Responsibilities:

Support CMO and Packaging categories through collaboration with cross-functional subject matter experts to achieve business, operational, quality, and performance objectives.
Lead cross-functional teams in evaluating and selecting CMOs for specific projects as required.
Partner with global stakeholders from Supply Chain, Packaging, CMC Manufacturing, and Quality on CMO supplier selection, negotiation, and ongoing management.
Collaborate with Operations Procurement, Legal, and Finance teams and report category outcomes to senior management.
Lead contract negotiations for Master Service Agreements (MSAs), Statements of Work (SOWs), and Supplier Proposals.
Own commercial negotiations including service fees, payment terms, milestones, and contractual responsibilities between BeiGene and CMOs.
Act as project manager for contract negotiations, working closely with Legal and business stakeholders to ensure adherence to timelines.
Develop risk mitigation strategy documents for N-level CMOs and N-1 sub-tier supply chain risks aligned to business requirements.
Ensure the overall health of CMO and partner relationships, driving strong collaboration and long-term value.
Drive continuous improvement initiatives across CMOs and sub-suppliers.
Lead and participate in CMO site visits as required.
Lead the creation of MSAs and contract amendments, ensuring alignment with the existing business relationship.
Participate in Business Operations Reviews and formal governance structures with CMOs and partners.
Proactively identify supplier and supply chain risks and execute risk mitigation and contingency plans.
Actively participate in CMO project meetings to proactively resolve relationship or delivery risks.
Drive proactive problem solving, status communication, and stakeholder collaboration across projects.
Conduct high-quality data analytics and generate routine supplier performance reports, including key issues and highlights.
Prepare regular operational performance summaries such as CFO scorecards, cost savings reports, and Financial Excellence trackers.
Enforce CMO procurement policies and procedures in alignment with key stakeholders.
Ensure primary and secondary packaging categories are managed using the same methodologies, strategies, and risk management principles applied to the CMO category.
Focus on assurance of supply, quality, regulatory compliance, cost, service, and innovation as core drivers of category management success.

