JD 5:

Key Responsibilities

Supplier Management:
Manage relationships with a diverse portfolio of pharmaceutical suppliers (CMOs, packaging partners, clinical/service vendors), ensuring clear communication, issue resolution, and continuous improvement.

Contract Negotiation Support:
Lead contract negotiations with suppliers to secure favorable terms, including pricing, service fees, quality commitments, service levels, and regulatory obligations.

Purchase Order Creation & Management:
Prepare, process, and verify purchase orders (POs) and supporting documentation; manage requisitions from internal pharma stakeholders.

Cost Optimization & Savings Delivery:
Identify and negotiate cost reduction opportunities, volume-based pricing, and long-term agreements to optimize total cost of ownership while maintaining quality and supply assurance.

Contract Lifecycle Management:
Oversee the full contract lifecycle including drafting, review, amendments, renewals, and ensuring compliance with contractual, quality, and regulatory requirements.

Cost Tracking & Budget Management:
Monitor and track category spend, ensuring alignment with approved budgets and financial targets.

Invoicing & Payment Management:
Manage obsolete POs, supplier accounts, and ensure accurate routing and processing of purchase requests (PRs) and invoices.

Supplier Performance Evaluation:
Regularly evaluate supplier performance against delivery, quality, compliance, service levels, and contractual KPIs.

Global Procurement Operations (Pharma):
Support global procurement operations for pharmaceutical manufacturing, packaging, and service categories, ensuring compliance with local regulations and internal policies.

Cross-functional Collaboration:
Work closely with Supply Chain, CMC Manufacturing, Quality, Regulatory, Finance, and Business stakeholders to align sourcing strategies with business needs and budget objectives.

Procurement Systems & Tools:
Utilize procurement and contract management systems to track supplier performance, contracts, spend, and cost-saving initiatives.

Documentation & Governance:
Review, update, and create SOPs, procurement guidelines, and knowledge base documentation related to pharma category management.

